    "created_at": "2012-10-22T13:18:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-10-22T13:18:40Z",
    "body": "You cannot break from a `do` because `do` does not require any sort of protocol, unlike `for`.  The best we could do is to make `break` equivalent to \"return\" from the closure---which perhaps we ought to do, but I am not sure.  There is no reason to think that the function will observe \"break-like\" semantics.\n",
