    "updated_at": "2013-03-22T16:09:41Z",
    "body": "(there are of course other options.  e.g. we could look into mitsuhiko's suggestion and change the calling convention so that invoking a closure implicitly passes along some number >1 of continuations, corresponding to different places control should shift in response to `continue` vs `break` vs `return`; but we would probably need to see some very convincing use-cases to motivate such a change.)\n",
