    "created_at": "2013-05-15T18:46:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-05-15T18:46:01Z",
    "body": "Yeah, I'm sensing this is more of a WONTFIX. We're landing those enhancements to the `for`-protocol we can (eg. 3e0400fb86170baff30282edcdccff73e243fd6e / #6223 ) but I think encoding arbitrary loop-label break targets into it as in #4131 is likely pushing it beyond the breaking point. And I agree with @nikomatsakis that there's not much we can do about `do` without demanding that it acquire a protocol-and-rewriting of its own (which would affect all users, on the off chance that they're called inside a loop)\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
