    "created_at": "2013-11-11T19:22:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-11-11T19:22:56Z",
    "body": "Even with the new `for` loop, this is still an issue\n\n``` rust\nfn foo(f: ||) {}  \n\nfn main() {       \n    loop {        \n        do foo {  \n            break;\n        }         \n    }             \n}                 \n```\n\nThat still gives the same error message, which is still misleading because it's inside of a `loop`\n",
